subSubSection.paragraph:
Lanzavecchia mangrovi
sp. n.
is similar to
L. coomansi ,
found in mangroves in Australia (
Nicholas & Stewart, 1984
), but differs in the longer body (L = 2.71–3.76 mm versus L = 2.2–2.9 mm in
L. coomansi
), shorter spicules ( 63–65 µm versus 72–88 µm in
L. coomansi
), longer prerectum ( 500–675 µm versus 262–310 µm in
L. coomansi
) and shorter distal portion of tail in relation to its proximal portion ( 0.6–0.8 versus 0.9–2.3 in
L. coomansi
) (
Nicholas, Stewart, 1984
).
